main event: On May 6, 1956, in Aliquippa, Pennsylvania, a sighting of seven silver baseball-sized objects in the sky was reported. They appeared for approximately one minute and then disappeared without any sound, moving south at an altitude of 8,000 to 10,000 ft.
interesting points: The objects were reported to be in sight for 5-10 minutes.
No photographs or visual content were included in the report.
The sighting was not being investigated due to the incomplete condition of the file, and it was suggested that further investigation would unlikely reveal valuable data.
The conclusion listed the event as 'unidentified,' with other possible explanations including 'probably satellite,' 'possibly balloon,' and 'insufficient data for evaluation.'
The sighting was also documented on radar, with details about altitude and speed provided.
